olive oil
1 courgette
2 clove garlic
1 packet soy sauce mix
1 packet ginger paste
½ tsp brown sugar
¼ cup water
1 packet green beans
1 packet Smooth Dory Fillets

• Thinly slice courgette into sticks. Trim and halve green beans.
• Finely chop garlic.
• In a small bowl, combine soy sauce mix, ginger paste, the brown sugar
and the water.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat.
• Cook courgette and green beans, tossing until tender, 4-5 minutes.
• Add garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer to a bowl and cover to keep warm.

TIP: Add a dash of water to the pan to help speed up the cooking process.

• Remove smooth dory fillets from packaging and pat dry with paper towel.
• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Season fish on both sides with salt and pepper.
• When oil is hot, cook fish in batches until just cooked through, 5-6 minutes each side.
• Remove pan from heat and add the soy-ginger mixture, turning fish
to coat.

TIP: White fish is cooked through when the centre turns from translucent to white.

• Divide soy-ginger glazed white fish and garlicky stir-fried greens
between plates.
• Spoon over any remaining glaze from the pan to serve. Enjoy!